A suffix is a morpheme (a unit of meaning) added to the end of a root, either a free morpheme (word that can stand by itself) or a bound morpheme (meaningful unit that cannot stand on its own). 

Would you argue that -ible is not a suffix in comestible or edible because ed- and comest- are not freestanding words?

